    <item>
      <title>Speedrun Practice Mod</title>
      <author>adrianRTA</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/626696</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/626696#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">a8b8fac7fcbf42ed45dc36622cea88a47df2bb47</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 22:54:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/694f21bf8f39f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/694f23266235e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/694f21b977372.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Full Initial Release&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: All NMG levels tweaked including some levels in Any% + 100% (all KO Arenas + Badge Marathon) as well&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Improvement&lt;/em&gt;: Item Park updated to include the Elephant Fruit pipe again and a Bubble Flower was added to the start&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Removal&lt;/em&gt;: Bowser's Rage Stage autoscroller removed for bossfight practice&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Custom Title Screen&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a Super Mario Bros. Wonder mod created for speedrunners that want to practice more efficiently than what the vanilla game offers, with the current changes optimizing practice for the &lt;b&gt;Any% No Major Glitches&lt;/b&gt; category. Some changes have been made to levels in the &lt;b&gt;Any%&lt;/b&gt; + &lt;b&gt;100%&lt;/b&gt; categories (including all KO Arenas + Badge Marathon) as well and our next major update plans to tweak the rest of the levels seen in &lt;b&gt;Any%&lt;/b&gt;!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Changes&lt;/h1&gt;If a level isn't listed here, it either hasn't been changed yet, or is not significant enough to have any changes to it. This is the case for most "Break Time!" and "Badge Challenge" levels.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;General&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Custom Title Screen Background&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An in-game timer is included in &lt;i&gt;every level&lt;/i&gt; including "Break Time!" and "Badge Challenge" levels that otherwise don't have any changes applied!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;World 1&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Welcome to the Flower Kingdom!&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Piranha Plants on Parade&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to note-block section before Secret Exit pipe&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scram, Skedaddlers!&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before grabbing shell for throwing at 3rd 10 coin, pipe after shell throw sends back to previous pipe&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Here Come the Hoppos&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before hitting shell for activating 3rd 10 coin, pipe right before Wonder Flower sends back to previous pipe&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sproings in the Twilight Forest&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cosmic Hoppos&lt;/b&gt; - Enter left subarea for 3nd 10 coin room, first pipe sends to section between 2 semi-solids before 1st 10 coin, second pipe sends to section before 2nd 10 coin, third pipe sends to section before Flagpole for Wonder Flower practice, pipe below that sends back to first pipe (SUBJECT TO CHANGE)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expert Badge Challenge Jet Run I&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section after Checkpoint Flag, first pipe at the end of the level sends back to the beginning, second pipe sends back to Checkpoint Flag.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pipe-Rock Plateau Palace&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to section before Checkpoint Flag, second pipes sends to pipe before Wonder Flower, third pipe sends to Bowser Jr. boss fight&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KO Arena Pipe-Rock Rumble&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes to send to each arena room, Elephant Fruit placed on spawn&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;World 2&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pokipede Pass&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower and 3rd 10 coin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Condarts Away!&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower (Note: Cycle will be off from RTA, use for practicing Wonder Flower entry)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Up 'n' Down with Puffy Lifts&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower and 3rd 10 coin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Jump! Jump! Jump!&lt;/b&gt; - Bubble flower near spawn, pipe at end of Wonder Section to quickly retry (Red on/off outline blocks placed over 3rd 10 coin for clarity during retries)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Countdown to Drop Down&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fluff-Puff Peaks Flying Battleship&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to 2nd 10 coin room, re-entering the same pipe sends to section before 2nd 10 coin room for entry practice (Note: Changed color of the pipe from white to green to signify that it can be entered)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fluff-Puff Peaks Palace&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower, second pipe sends to Bowser Jr. boss fight&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KO Arena Fluff-Puff Kerfluff&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes to send to each arena room, Elephant Fruit placed on spawn&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Search Party Puzzling Park&lt;/b&gt; - Pipe with respawning Elephant Fruits placed at start&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;World 3&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Hoppycat Trial: Hop, Hop, and Awaaay&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to short section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Anglefish Trial: Ready, Aim, Fly!&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to 2nd 10 coin room, second pipe sends to 3rd 10 coin room&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Midway Trial: Hop to It&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to end of the level&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Sharp Trial: Launch to Victory&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to short section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Search Party An Empty Park?&lt;/b&gt; - Pipe with respawning Elephant Fruits placed at start&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;World 4&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Armads on the Roll&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before 3rd 10 coin and Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ninji Jump Party&lt;/b&gt; - Bubble Flower placed right before gate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bloomps of the Desert Skies&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Valley Fulla Snootles&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before 2nd 10 coin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sunbaked Desert Palace&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower, second pipe sends to Bowser Jr. boss fight&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KO Arena Sunbaked Skirmish&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes to send to each arena room, Elephant Fruit placed on spawn, Drill Mushroom placed between the top two pipes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;World 5&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Upshroom Downshroom&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to subarea with Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Beware of the Rifts&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Taily's Toxic Pond&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to Checkpoint Flag&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Light-Switch Mansion&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to Checkpoint Flag&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;An Uncharted Area: Wubba Ruins&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Another Uncharted Area: Swaying Ruins&lt;/b&gt; - Starting door sends to subarea before Wonder Flower (Room 6)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;A Final Uncharted Area: Poison Ruins&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to subarea with Wonder Flower, starting gap sends to subarea following the falling cutscene&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KO Arena Fungi Funk&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes to send to each arena room, Drill Mushroom placed on spawn, Bubble Flower placed atop 4th pipe&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;World 6&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Where the Rrrumbas Rule&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Raarghs in the Ruins&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to subarea with Wonder Flower (Note: Cycle will be off from RTA, use for practicing Wonder Flower entry)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pull, Turn, Burn&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Deep Magma Bog Palace&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to first Checkpoint Flag, second pipe sends to Bowser Jr. boss fight&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KO Arena Magma Flare-Up&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes to send to each arena room, Elephant Fruit placed on spawn&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Search Party: Item Park&lt;/b&gt; - Added mechanism that allows for the same cycle between initial level load and level restart. Extremely useful for RTA cycle practice.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Petal Isles&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Robbird Cove&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to pipe before 1st 10 coin, second pipe sends to section before Checkpoint Flag&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Blewbird Roost&lt;/b&gt; - First red pipe sends to section shortly after 1st 10 coin (with reset pipe after walljump), first yellow pipe and second red pipe send to subarea, second yellow pipe sends to top of subarea near Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Jewel-Block Cave&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before 2nd 10 coin room and Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Petal Isles Flying Battleship&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to 2nd 10 coin room&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Maw-Maw Mouthful&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Muncher Fields&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KO Arena Petal Meddle&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes to send to each arena room, Elephant Fruit placed on spawn&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Missile Meg Mayhem&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to next subarea&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;High-Voltage Gauntlet&lt;/b&gt; - Starting pipe sends to section before Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Evade the Seeker Bullet Bills!&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to section before 1st 10 coin, second pipe sends to second sub area with 3rd 10 coin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;KnuckleFest: Bowser's Blazing Beats&lt;/b&gt; - First pipe sends to section before first Checkpoint Flag, second pipe sends to subarea with Wonder Flower&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Final Battle! Bowser's Rage Stage&lt;/b&gt; - Player spawn set where the checkpoint used to be, Bubble Flower and Elephant Fruit placed in front of the spawn (No more autoscroller!)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Special World&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Final Test: Wonder Gauntlet&lt;/b&gt; - Elephant Fruit and Bubble Flower added at spawn&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Final-Final Test: Badge Marathon&lt;/b&gt; - Added pipes for each individual room, with accompanying badge signs for clarity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Credits&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Codek&lt;/b&gt; – Most level edits from W3-8, edited in-game timer position, bug fixes, GitHub repository owner.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;adrianRTA&lt;/b&gt; – Custom Title Screen background, changes for NMG levels from Welcome to the Flower Kingdom! to Jump! Jump! Jump!, Upshroom Downshroom changes, Search Party: Item Park mechanism idea and implementation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Theia // FrozenMuncher&lt;/b&gt; - &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/570723"&gt;Bindable Actor Pack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/theia-mly/Fushigi" target="_blank"&gt;Fushigi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; contributors for making all of these changes possible with ease&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://discord.gg/jBtBW22xuu" target="_blank"&gt;WonderLand Discord server&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; for helping us out when we had issues&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
